{{Infobox book | name = Mastery | translator = | image = Mastery Cover.jpg | caption = Hardcover edition | author =[[Robert Greene (American author)|Robert Greene]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | subject = Strategy, self-help, philosophy | genre = Non-fiction | publisher = [[Viking Adult]] | pub_date = November 13, 2012 | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = 352 | isbn = | oclc = | preceded_by = [[The 50th Law]] | followed_by = }}
'''''Mastery''''' is the fifth book by the American author [[Robert Greene (American author)|Robert Greene]].<ref name=cnnmoney>{{cite web|last=Capouya|first=John|title=Zen and the art of global domination|url=http://features.blogs.fortune.cnn.com/2012/11/09/mastery-robert-greene/|publisher=CNN Money|date=November 9, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121113062422/http://features.blogs.fortune.cnn.com/2012/11/09/mastery-robert-greene/|archivedate=November 13, 2012|df=}}</ref> The book examines the lives of great historical figures—such as [[Charles Darwin]], [[Mozart]], and [[Henry Ford]]—and contemporary leaders—such as [[Paul Graham (computer programmer)|Paul Graham]] and [[Freddie Roach (boxing)|Freddie Roach]]—and distills the traits and universal ingredients that made them masters.<ref name=masterybook>{{cite book |title=Mastery |first=Robert |last=Greene |publisher=Viking |location= |year=2012 |isbn=0670024961 |pages= |url=}}</ref><ref>Ben Thapa. [http://www.bloodyelbow.com/2012/11/12/3634848/interviewing-robert-greene-about-mastery-hustle-fear-boxing-and-mma Interviewing Robert Greene about Mastery, Hustle, Fear, Boxing and MMA]. ''Bloody Elbow''. November 12, 2012.</ref><ref name=huffpost>{{cite news|title='Mastery' By Robert Greene Wants Its Readers To Achieve Greatness (VIDEO) |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/10/16/mastery-by-robert-greene-_n_1969937.html|newspaper=Huffington Post|date=October 16, 2012|first=Andrew|last=Losowsky}}</ref> The book was published on November 13, 2012 by [[Viking Adult]].
==Origins== The book originated from a realization that Greene had in 2007.<ref name=powerseductionwar>Greene, Robert. [http://powerseductionandwar.com/hidden-powers-my-next-book-mastery-part-1/ Hidden Powers & My Next Book: Mastery: Part 1]. ''Power Seduction and War''. October 1, 2012.</ref> In writing and researching his first four books (including ''[[The 48 Laws of Power]]''), Greene concluded that all the people he studied and wrote about—no matter their field, culture, or moment in history—followed the same pathway to [[Power (social and political)|power]].<ref name=powerseductionwar/> After finishing his fourth book, ''[[The 50th Law]]'', Greene began to examine this concept in depth and decided that it would be the focus of his next book.<ref name=powerseductionwar/><ref>[http://www.33voices.com/robert-greene Ten Inspirational Moments from Robert Greene]. ''[[33voices]]''.</ref>
==Synopsis== ''Mastery'' explains how to become a leader in any given field by examining the lives and pathways to success of historical masters such as Mozart, Einstein and Darwin, as well as "living masters" which Greene interviewed—including [[Paul Graham (computer programmer)|Paul Graham]], [[Freddie Roach (boxing)|Freddie Roach]], [[Santiago Calatrava]], [[Temple Grandin]], [[Yoky Matsuoka]], [[V.S. Ramachandran]], [[Teresita Fernandez]], [[Cesar Rodriguez (USAF pilot)|Cesar Rodriguez]], and [[Daniel Everett]].<ref name=masterybook/><ref name=nytimes>{{cite news|last=Kurutz|first=Steven|title=Renovate Like a Master|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/11/08/garden/robert-greene-on-renovating-like-a-master.html?pagewanted=all&_r=0|newspaper=New York Times|date=November 7, 2012}}</ref><ref>[http://www.geekwire.com/2012/excerpt-yoky-matsuoka-created-modern-robotic-hand/ How Yoky Matsuoka created the modern robotic hand, and what the rest of us can learn from her] ''GeekWire''. November 12, 2012.</ref><ref>Thapa, Ben. [http://www.bloodyelbow.com/2012/11/13/3639184/freddie-roach-and-manny-pacquiao-excerpt-robert-greene-mastery-boxing Freddie Roach and Manny Pacquiao, Excerpt From Robert Greene’s Mastery]. ''Bloody Elbow''. November 13, 2012.</ref>
==Reception== ''Mastery'' reached #6 on [[The New York Times Best Seller List|''The New York Times'' Bestseller list]] and was featured in ''[[The New York Times]]'', ''[[CNN Money]]'', ''[[The Huffington Post]]'', ''[[Business Insider]]'', ''[[Forbes]]'', ''[[Management Today]]'', and ''[[Fast Company (magazine)|Fast Company]]''.<ref name="cnnmoney"/><ref name=huffpost/><ref name=nytimes/><ref name=businessinsider>{{cite web|last=Groth|first=Aimee|title=27 Tips For Mastering Anything|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/robert-greenes-mastery-2012-11?op=1|publisher=Business Insider|date=November 2, 1012}}</ref><ref name=Forbes>{{cite news|last=Bradt|first=George|title=Beyond 10,000 Hours: The Constant Pursuit of Mastery|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/georgebradt/2012/11/08/beyond-10000-hours-the-constant-pursuit-of-mastery/|publisher=Forbes|date=November 8, 2012}}</ref><ref name=ManagementToday>Chamorro-Premuzic, Tomas. [http://www.managementtoday.co.uk/books/1155920/book-review-mastery-robert-greene/ Book review: Mastery, by Robert Greene]. ''Management Today''. November 1, 2012.</ref><ref>Robert Greene. [http://www.fastcompany.com/3002810/aha-moments-made-paul-grahams-y-combinator-possible The Aha! Moments That Made Paul Grahms Y Combinator Possible]. ''Fast Company''. November 12, 2012.</ref><ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/11/15/mastery-by-robert-greene-_n_2126127.html ‘Mastery’ By Robert Greene: How to Become a Master in Your Chosen Field]. ''Huffington Post''. November 15, 2012.</ref><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/best-sellers-books/2012-12-02/hardcover-advice/list.html Best Sellers: Advice and Misc.].''The New York Times''. November 26, 2012.</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://books.usatoday.com/book/robert-greene-mastery/l48492 |title=Mastery |newspaper=USA Today}}</ref>
